# STM32 BluePill — Sensor Hub

STM32F103C8T6 sensor aggregation node. Reads three DHT11 temperature/humidity sensors via FreeRTOS tasks, logs data and fault events to FRAM over I2C, and transmits JSON to the BeagleBone via UART2.

## Hardware

- **MCU:** STM32F103C8T6 (64KB flash, 20KB RAM)
- **Sensors:** DHT11 on PA4, PA5, PA6
- **FRAM:** MB85RC256V via I2C1
- **UART1:** Debug output
- **UART2:** JSON output to BeagleBone

## Source Files

| File | Description |
|:-----|:------------|
| `Core/Src/main.c` | FreeRTOS tasks, sensor polling, JSON output |
| `Core/Src/freertos.c` | FreeRTOS kernel init |
| `Core/Src/stm32f1xx_it.c` | Fault handlers with crash log integration |
| `UserCore/Src/dht11_driver.c` | DHT11 1-wire driver |
| `UserCore/Src/fram_driver.c` | FRAM I2C driver |
| `UserCore/Src/crash_log.c` | FRAM-backed crash logging |

## Build

```bash
cd stm32-bluepill

# Configure (once)
cmake -B build -DCMAKE_TOOLCHAIN_FILE=cmake/gcc-arm-none-eabi.cmake

# Build
cmake --build build -j$(nproc)

# Build with crash halt (JTAG debugging)
cmake --build build --clean-first -- -j$(nproc) CFLAGS="-DCRASH_HALT=1"
```

## Flash

```bash
# ST-Link
st-flash write build/stm32-bluepill.elf 0x08000000
```

## Monitor

```bash
minicom -D /dev/ttyACM0 -b 115200
```

## CubeMX Regeneration

The `.ioc` is configured with `DeletePrevious=false`, `BackupPrevious=true`, `KeepUserCode=true`. User code inside `/* USER CODE BEGIN ... */` blocks survives regeneration. After any regeneration verify with:

```bash
diff Core/Src/main.c Core/Src/Backup/main.c
diff Core/Src/stm32f1xx_it.c Core/Src/Backup/stm32f1xx_it.c
```
